    <div xml:id="PN361">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kāreti rurumi ṉuraṟik kalleṉa</l>
<l>vāruyirk kalamaru mārāk kūṟṟa</l>
<l>niṉvara vañcalaṉ mātō naṉpala</l>
<l>kēḷvi muṟṟiya vēḷvi yantaṇark</l>
<l>karuṅkala nīroṭu citaṟip peruntakait</l>
<l>tāyiṉaṉṟu palarkkīttut</l>
<l>teruṇaṭai mākaḷiṟṟoṭu taṉ</l>
<l>ṉaruḷpāṭunarkku naṉkaruḷiyu</l>
<l>muruṇaṭai ..................ṉṟataṉ</l>
<l>ṟāḷcērunark kiṉitīttum</l>
<l>purimālaiyar pāṭiṉikkup</l>
<l>polantāmaraip pūmpāṇaroṭu</l>
<l>kalantaḷaiiya nīḷirukkaiyāṟ</l>
<l>poṟaiyoṭu <supplied>ER: malinta kaṟpiṉ</supplied> māṉōkkiṉ</l>
<l>villeṉa vilaṅkiya puruvattu valleṉa</l>
<l>nalki ṉāvañcu muḷḷeyiṟṟu makaḷi</l>
<l>ralku ṟāṅkā vacaii melleṉa</l>
<l><supplied>ER: tēṟal</supplied> polaṅkalat tēnti</l>
<l>yamiḻteṉa maṭuppa mānti yikaḻvila</l>
<l>ṉillā vulakattu......... mainī</l>
<l>colla vēṇṭā.......... muntaṟinta</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Insatiable Death who roars like the thunder facing the rainy season,</l>
<l>noisily, [and] is upsetting to [people’s] precious lives, (1f.)</l>
<l>won’t he be afraid of your coming, (3a-c)</l>
<l>the paragon, having, in a sacrifice that is completed with a good many</l>
<l>śruti [verses], splashed out precious vessels to brahmins along with water. (3d-5)</l>
<l>Giving good things to many like a mother (6)</l>
<l>being very gracious to those who sing his grace (8)</l>
<l>with clear(?)-gaited big elephant bulls, (9)</l>
<l>giving what is sweet to those who join his feet (10)</l>
<l>that ended……………….rolling gait (9)</l>
<l>offering golden vessels [of toddy] (18)</l>
<l>to songstresses who have garlands in strands, (11)</l>
<l>on [his] tall seat where he freely mingles (13)</l>
<l>with bards with golden lotus flowers, (12)</l>
<l>resting softly when the hips don’t endure  (17)</l>
<l>of women with thorn teeth feared by [their] tongues, if they grant (16)</l>
<l>quickly the brows that lie athwart like bows, (15)</l>
<l>with deer glances, [with abundant fidelity] along with forebearance, (14)</l>
<l>eating when [something] is offered as ambrosia he is without reproach. (19)</l>
<l>in the world that does not last …. </l>
<l>it is not necessary for you to say………….. that was known before (20f.)</l>
</lg>
